wikipedia_page.main: Ivor Grosvenor Guest, 2nd Viscount Wimborne,  (21 February 1903 – 7 January 1967) was a British politician.

response: On 10 February 1902, he married at St Peter's Church, Eaton Square, London, the Honourable Alice Grosvenor (1880–1948), daughter of Robert Grosvenor, 2nd Baron Ebury. They had one son, Ivor Guest, 2nd Viscount Wimborne, and two daughters, Rosemary and Cynthia.
